Very dense sample! Tons of diatom chains. Also a few less common objects - e.g. a dead(?) copepod, and an uncommon chain of high-aspect-ratio diatoms, and a nearly-opaque blobby organism which deformed itself in an interesting way. And lots of individual cicular plankton (either centric diatoms or maybe a dinoflagellate like Pyrocystis?)
